Metadata: Six new diterpene isonitriles from the sponge "Acanthella cavernosa"

The kalihinols and related compounds are diterpenoids from sponges of the genus "Acanthella" that contain two, and often three, isonitrile functionalitiesâ€‹. Members of this series of compounds have been reported to have antimicrobial, antifungal, cytotoxic, and anthelmintic properties. This paper reports the isolation of seven diterpene isonitriles from a specimen of "Acanthella cavernosa" collected in the Seychelles.
